      "text": "23. LET THE PLAN GO *",
      "id": "34e19af5009d9cb6",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "You have a <i>[[SEMINAR PLAN]]</i> and you try to stick to it. This can create a kind of inflexibility. At sometime during the sessions, the need will arise, to do something unplanned because a participant asks a question that is not really part of your plan. You have enough BUFFERS, so there is no temporary constraints.\n  ",
      "id": "4f0645c094f003f9",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "&lt;center&gt;❖ ❖ ❖&lt;/center&gt;",
      "id": "fa9dfd51b8a0ceb0",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "<b>Therefore</b>, let the plan go. Diverge from the plan and improvise the parts that are necessary to cover the unplanned topic. This is a good way to <i>[[ADAPT TO PARTICIPANTS BACKGROUND]]</i>. It is important to have a <i>[[SEMINAR PLAN]]</i>, to be able to return to that plan after you have finished the unplanned topic. Thus, the insertion of an unplanned topic will not result in chaos.\n  ",
      "id": "3a0de1a5829529af",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "You could either insert the topic \"in-line\" and answer it immediately. Then it is good to choose another presentation medium, e.g. the flipchart if you use transparencies for the planned topics.\n  ",
      "id": "ca74e4447454a8c6",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "You could also postpone the unplanned topic until you have finished with a reasonable section of the plan. To make sure that the topic is not forgotten, it might make sense to add the unplanned topic to the overview or to the <i>[[RESULTS AND PROBLEMS]]</i>.\n  ",
